  "prompt": "What is voltage regulation formula?",
  "response": "Voltage regulation typically refers to the change in voltage magnitude from no-load to full-load conditions. The formula for voltage regulation in the context of transformers is:\n\n\\[ \\text{Voltage Regulation} = \\frac{V_{nl} - V_{fl}}{V_{fl}} \\times 100\\% \\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( V_{nl} \\) is the no-load voltage (secondary voltage when there is no load connected).\n- \\( V_{fl} \\) is the full-load voltage (secondary voltage when the full load is connected).\n\nThe percentage gives an idea of how much the voltage drops when the transformer is loaded.",
